  "prompt": "How should I tell my husband that I'm pregnant? We weren't trying",
  "response": "Here are some thoughtful approaches to sharing unexpected pregnancy news:\n\n1. Choose a comfortable, private setting\n- At home\n- When you're both relaxed\n- Not during a stressful time\n\n2. Be direct and honest\n- Start with \"I have something important to tell you\"\n- Share the news straightforwardly\n- Use \"we're pregnant\" or \"I'm pregnant\"\n\n3. Give space for initial reactions\n- Your husband might be surprised\n- Allow him time to process the information\n- Be prepared for various emotional responses\n\n4. Share your feelings\n- Express your own emotions\n- Whether you're excited, nervous, or uncertain\n- Be vulnerable and open\n\n5. Discuss next steps together\n- Talk about practical considerations\n- Financial planning\n- Healthcare\n- Living arrangements\n\n6. Potential conversation starters:\n- \"I just found out I'm pregnant. I want us to talk about this together.\"\n- \"We're going to have a baby. How are you feeling?\"\n- \"I have some unexpected news that will change our lives.\"\n\n7. Have medical confirmation/documentation ready if helpful\n\n8. Be patient and supportive of each other's initial reactions\n\nRemember, open communication and mutual support are key during this significant life moment.",
